<!--
THE QUESTION EVERY SHAREHOLDER, USER, AND COMPANY SHOULD ASK:

The Window Management API is marketed as "free."

Is it really?

COMPANIES PAY:
- Technical consultants to change backend infrastructure
- Developer time learning the new API (vs using window.open())
- Permission prompt rejection (how many users will they lose)
- Ongoing maintenance (Chrome-only = vendor lock-in)

USERS PAY:
- Privacy loss (permission prompts = more data collection)
- Worse UX (chromeless windows, permission friction)
- Exclusion (Firefox/Safari users blocked)
- Higher prices (companies pass costs to customers)

How long before these costs are passed to the end user?

That's you, sitting at the bottom of the Silicon Extraction Stack.
-->

